## Tier 2 — High-value experiments (close the GPT/Opus gap)

Order by ratio of reviewer-impact to engineering cost.

0. **[DONE 2026-04-30] Split benchmark.cpp into per-scenario binaries.** The 4386-line monolithic `benchmark.cpp` is gone. New layout: `benchmark/Common.hpp` (shared infrastructure: `Data`, `BenchmarkContext`, `TimedBuild`, `TimedQueries`, `run_scenario_cache_{dependent,independent}`, `run_storage_scenario`), `benchmark/Verify.hpp` (verifier driver), `benchmark/Scenarios.hpp` (data factories), `verify.cpp` (root, runs all 5 verifiers), and 25 self-contained source files in `benchmark/scenarios/` (grid, multiple-survey-2-l..12-fortynine, storage, each × cache-{dependent,independent}). No environment variables: scenario, seed count, query cap, and algorithm subset are hard-coded per binary. Makefile rewritten with per-scenario targets (`benchmark-X-cache-{dependent,independent}`), `benchmark-grid`, `benchmark-cache-sweep`, `benchmark-storage`, `benchmark-5D`, and a top-level `benchmark` target that runs the full reproduction suite. Old shell scripts `run/{benchmarks,benchmark-stress,storage-benchmarks,verify-combinations}.sh` deleted; the `run/` folder is gone entirely (the `result_dir` helper has been inlined into the Makefile and `roaring_library` was made obsolete by the Makefile's own libroaring.a rules). README.md and IPT.tex reproducibility paragraph updated.

10. **Unordered-input end-to-end construction benchmark** (Opus M3, GPT, TODO). Build IPT and SortedPoints from the same unsorted point list; report total wall time. Directly fixes the `N/7` claim. Lowest-risk new measurement; reuses benchmark.cpp infrastructure.
11. **Hit-vs-miss `pos` benchmark** (Opus M7, TODO). The miss path already exists in `IPT.ipp` / `Cuboid.ipp`; add a workload variant in benchmark.cpp that mixes hits and misses and report both. Removes the bias accusation against SortedPoints `lower_bound`.
