    New section:results-stress-5d + table:stress-5d-summary in IPT.tex, populated from the 18 c0r1e1l0 stress runs by a new extractor plot/stress-summary.cpp wired through the Makefile (EXTRA_EXTRACTORS, PLOTS). Reports κ, IPT byte size, construct rate, pos/at throughput, and select/restrict latency for the multiple-survey-9-5d 5D scenario (47×44×41×125×80, 92.26M unique points). The workloads subsection now cross-references it instead of relying on rhetorical narrowing alone.
13. **[DONE 2026-04-30] Flat-layout / mmap experiment** (Opus M2). Implemented as `make benchmark-storage`, sourced from `benchmark/scenarios/storage.cpp`, which calls `run_storage_scenario` in `benchmark/Common.hpp`. For each of the structured scenarios `multiple-survey-{2-l..8-threed}`, all 8 storage-capable algorithms (IPT greedy-plus-merge, SortedPoints, DenseBitset, BlockBitmap, Roaring, LexRun, RowCSR-k1, RowCSR-km) are serialized to disk, the page cache is dropped, the file is mmap'd, and time-to-first-response and bytes-on-disk are recorded.  Two cache combinations are produced: `storage-c0r0e0l0.txt` (no caches, minimal IPT footprint) and `storage-c0r1e1l0.txt` (reference). The storage runs are now part of `make benchmark` (the previous suite did not include them).

